                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-746" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY PERKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter. On the 3rd of August, I left my tools at Mr. Berkley's shop, in Gray's-inn-lane, at half-past seven o'clock in the evening, under the bench against the window, in the front shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-747" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-747" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-747" type="surname" value="BANFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-747" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BANFIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in that house, and am a tailor. About ten minutes past eight o'clock I was in the back place, and saw the prisoner through the slit of the door, he made a dart into the shop, and fetched out a basket of tools as light as he could—I made after him, and took him in Liquorpond-street—I said, "Is this your property?"—he said, "No;" and dropped it, and took to his heels—I caught him and brought him back to the basket—I did not know him before.</p>
